Dockside cranes sit idle as the Harbor Saints call a “safety strike,” really a cover to move their blackmail ledgers before the Marrow Society’s survey crews start marking basements for a new “flood-control” tunnel. Rumors say a ledger page with Vice Bureau payoffs is missing, and Saints enforcers are shaking down bartenders and singers to find who lifted it. Tonight, the Vice Bureau plans a headline raid on the Velvet Lark—Eve’s club—while Detective Halden (married, compromised) begs for a warning he can’t be seen receiving. In the fog, Marrow men offer Eve a clean name for one delivery.

